1
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:10,400
Where were you
on the night of the fire?

2
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:14,667
As far as you remember,
what happened before the fire?

3
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:17,433
You cannot just accuse Edward
like that.

4
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:19,533
None of you had the motive
to do it.

5
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:22,100
Because he was the only one
angry at me and our family.

6
00:00:22,233 --> 00:00:24,767
Dad, Edward would never do that!

7
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:29,133
Are you really going to fight me
on this, Paolo?

8
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:31,300
The fight has already begun.

9
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:34,300
I hope you don't regret
what you're doing.

10
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:35,767
Edward is innocent.

11
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:37,600
What are you doing here?

12
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,167
I'm here for my child.

13
00:00:39,300 --> 00:00:41,533
Why? Do you have a problem
with that?

14
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:44,767
Be thankful I still can't
completely destroy you.

15
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:48,233
You still need to see me
destroy your child.

16
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:52,800
Don't destroy
the Torrecampo name.

17
00:00:55,933 --> 00:00:59,133
You're still so proud of being
a Torrecampo, aren't you?

18
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:02,133
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

19
00:01:03,767 --> 00:01:04,833
Where do you think you'll end up

20
00:01:04,967 --> 00:01:06,933
once that name is taken away
from you?

21
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,333
What do you mean?

22
00:01:08,467 --> 00:01:10,800
Whoever really burned
the mansion,

23
00:01:10,933 --> 00:01:13,067
I truly hope they feel remorse.

24
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,300
Ms. Yolly.

25
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,867
She saw me enter the room.

26
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,967
Ma'am Marj,
what are you doing here?

27
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:22,700
I think I may have a solution

28
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:24,533
to get his case dismissed.

29
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:29,833
Sir Greg will surely withdraw
the case and release Edward

30
00:01:29,967 --> 00:01:31,833
once he learns the truth.

31
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,567
[DRAMATIC INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

32
00:02:18,967 --> 00:02:21,567
You cannot just accuse Edward

33
00:02:21,700 --> 00:02:24,133
just because you found his watch
there.

34
00:02:24,267 --> 00:02:27,267
If that's the case, then charge
everyone who owns items there,

35
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,933
which includes all of us.

36
00:02:29,067 --> 00:02:32,333
None of you had a motive
to do it. Only him.

37
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:34,600
Because he was the only one
angry at me and our family.

38
00:02:35,633 --> 00:02:38,867
I don't think Edward
would risk his family,

39
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,867
especially Ashley.

40
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,100
That's a perfect excuse,
isn't it?

41
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:46,867
His family was there
when it happened.

42
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Of course he'd have a plan
about that.

43
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:51,900
That's ridiculous.

44
00:02:52,033 --> 00:02:54,133
Dad, Edward would never do that!

45
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:58,767
Are you really going to fight me
on this, Paolo?

46
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:02,233
Yes, Dad, because what
you're doing is no longer right.

47
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:14,900
And who are you to tell me
that I'm wrong?

48
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,900
You have no right to question
my decisions!

49
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:22,933
And Edward is my brother,
whether he is my blood or not.

50
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:26,367
And I believe in him.
That's why I will help him.

51
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:31,467
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:32,867
Careful, Paolo.

53
00:03:35,233 --> 00:03:38,567
You better shut up now
and pick the right side.

54
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:42,067
If you don't want to end up
like that bastard Edward.

55
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:44,067
No, Dad.

56
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,300
You be careful.

57
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:48,700
We are the only family
you have left.

58
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:51,233
And if you force us
to pick sides,

59
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:55,033
Dad, believe me,
you will be left with nothing.

60
00:03:55,200 --> 00:04:05,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

61
00:04:10,133 --> 00:04:13,067
I hope you don't regret
what you're doing.

62
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:17,533
Edward is innocent,
and I know you know that.

63
00:04:17,667 --> 00:04:22,467
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

64
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:30,300
What time is it, Attorney?

65
00:04:30,433 --> 00:04:32,767
Why haven't we gone
to the inquest yet?

66
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:34,467
Ash can't be left alone
for too long.

67
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,667
- Edward.
- Pao.

68
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:40,033
Pao, Marj, thank you
for sending the lawyer.

69
00:04:40,167 --> 00:04:41,233
You're welcome.

70
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:44,100
What are you doing here?

71
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:45,633
I'm here for my son.

72
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:47,467
Why? Do you have a problem
with that?

73
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:51,533
We're here for Edward.

74
00:04:51,667 --> 00:04:54,133
This isn't the time to fight.

75
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:56,233
He needs us right now.

76
00:04:56,367 --> 00:04:57,533
She's right.

77
00:04:57,667 --> 00:05:00,433
Thea, please.
Let's call a ceasefire for now.

78
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:10,467
Does that mean he's siding with
his brother and not his father?

79
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:13,067
This is not about
choosing sides.

80
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:16,800
But Mr. Paolo Torrecampo
believes in his brother.

81
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:19,833
And he will do everything
to clear him.

82
00:05:23,067 --> 00:05:24,800
Yes, Dad.

83
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,900
That's your mistress.

84
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:31,600
The woman who ruined our lives.

85
00:05:40,267 --> 00:05:41,933
That is your child.

86
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:48,233
The person I will bring down
and destroy.

87
00:05:48,367 --> 00:05:52,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,200
Paolo.

89
00:05:56,167 --> 00:06:00,000
You made it clear to the press
that you're not siding with dad.

90
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:02,800
Aren't you afraid
you'll end up fighting?

91
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:04,767
He'll forgive me anyway.

92
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:06,467
I'm his favorite son, right?

93
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
To dad, you're his only son.

94
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:18,367
Well, in all seriousness,
the fight has already begun.

95
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:22,467
But maybe dad realized that...

96
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:25,500
he can't afford
to lose another son.

97
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:28,867
This wouldn't have happened
if only he had been fair to us.

98
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,567
You know what?

99
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:37,533
All my life,

100
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:40,600
I felt so lucky
being a Torrecampo.

101
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:42,867
Because I got everything
I wanted, right?

102
00:06:44,033 --> 00:06:45,433
But...

103
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:49,767
now I'll use my surname
to do something good.

104
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,800
And you'll be the first
to benefit from it, okay?

105
00:06:56,467 --> 00:06:57,733
Thank you, Paolo.

106
00:07:01,033 --> 00:07:02,700
We'll take that off.

107
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:10,433
Don't be angry with me, Dad.

108
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:15,033
I didn't commit this crime.

109
00:07:18,100 --> 00:07:21,133
I didn't commit this crime.

110
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:25,500
It was you.

111
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:29,133
It was you and your mistress!

112
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:32,833
[WHIMPERING]

113
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:43,467
Be thankful I still can't
destroy you completely.

114
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:47,000
You still need to witness me
destroy your child.

115
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:08:06,067 --> 00:08:07,733
So, while waiting
for the prosecutor,

117
00:08:07,867 --> 00:08:10,133
I just want to make sure
that we are aligned and ready

118
00:08:10,267 --> 00:08:12,667
for the questions that might
be thrown at you, Edward.

119
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:15,400
Okay? So, I'll ask you
some sample questions, okay?

120
00:08:15,533 --> 00:08:16,567
Okay.

121
00:08:16,700 --> 00:08:19,500
Where were you
on the night of the fire?

122
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:20,467
Just at home?

123
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,700
<i> Dad.</i>

124
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:25,667
As far as you remember,
what happened before the fire?

125
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:27,933
<i> Dad.</i>

126
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,000
I remember...

127
00:08:31,133 --> 00:08:33,267
I was very upset at that time.

128
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:38,533
Because dad and I were fighting.

129
00:08:38,667 --> 00:08:39,767
<i> You'll still side with Paolo</i>

130
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:41,633
<i>even though
I'm the one wronged here?</i>

131
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:46,033
<i>This house should burn!
Because this house is hell!</i>

132
00:08:46,167 --> 00:08:47,633
About what?

133
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:53,000
About Paolo and Thea's video.

134
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,333
[MOANING]

135
00:08:55,467 --> 00:08:57,567
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

136
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:05,167
Anyway, I drank alcohol.

137
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:06,533
But I fell asleep right away

138
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:09,400
because the alcohol hit me
quickly.

139
00:09:13,533 --> 00:09:16,700
Is there anyone
who can confirm that?

140
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:21,200
<i>My god.
Sir Edward, what did you do?</i>

141
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:23,733
<i>- I'll clean this up.
- No.</i>

142
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,233
<i> Just leave it like that.</i>

143
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:27,600
Ms. Yolly.

144
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:30,600
<i>- Someone might see it.
- Then let them see it.</i>

145
00:09:32,433 --> 00:09:34,333
She saw me enter the room.

146
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:37,967
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

147
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:54,767
Sorry about my place.

148
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,533
It's just small.

149
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:58,467
I'm only staying here
temporarily.

150
00:09:58,600 --> 00:09:59,567
You know how it is.

151
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,633
But that's okay.

152
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:04,900
At least you no longer have
to stay here.

153
00:10:05,033 --> 00:10:06,933
Especially now that your name
has been cleared

154
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:08,500
thanks to Sir Edward.

155
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,400
But Sir Edward is pitiful too.

156
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:14,833
Because just when
Ma'am Ashley got sick,

157
00:10:14,967 --> 00:10:16,233
that's when he was jailed.

158
00:10:16,367 --> 00:10:17,567
Yeah, that's true.

159
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:20,100
Could he have been framed too?

160
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:22,200
Like Ms. Yolly?

161
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:23,400
How was she framed?

162
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:27,000
Maybe someone deliberately
planted the watch

163
00:10:27,133 --> 00:10:29,433
among the evidence.

164
00:10:29,567 --> 00:10:32,900
Oh, dear, whoever truly burned
the mansion,

165
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:35,067
I really hope they feel guilty.

166
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:37,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,733
Weng, please eat first.

168
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:46,267
Eat this. You might lose weight.

169
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,067
I'll just take it with me.
Thank you, Ms. Yolly.

170
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,333
You and your takeaways.

171
00:10:50,467 --> 00:10:53,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

172
00:10:57,567 --> 00:11:00,333
I really thought she went back
to the province.

173
00:11:00,467 --> 00:11:02,933
Good thing she's still here
in Manila.

174
00:11:03,067 --> 00:11:08,067
Maybe she couldn't really leave
because she's wanted.

175
00:11:08,233 --> 00:11:11,300
But thank God, she's safe.

176
00:11:11,433 --> 00:11:14,167
At least she doesn't have
to hide anymore.

177
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:16,567
Did you see Ms. Yolly?

178
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,167
Did you talk to her?
Where is she?

179
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:20,033
Well, Marj...

180
00:11:20,167 --> 00:11:21,400
Weng, where is she?

181
00:11:25,033 --> 00:11:26,667
Weng, Cheche, I'm begging you.

182
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:29,533
Please tell me
where Ms. Yolly is.

183
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:32,567
You yourselves said
she's safe from the police.

184
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:34,500
You have nothing to fear.

185
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,500
I'm begging you.

186
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:41,500
Ms. Yolly is the only one who
can prove Edward is innocent.

187
00:11:41,667 --> 00:11:44,433
Please, help him.

188
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:48,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

189
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:57,467
<i>My client strongly denies
those accusations.</i>

190
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,733
He is not guilty
of those allegations.

191
00:11:59,867 --> 00:12:01,333
He is innocent.

192
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,900
You'll get through this, Dad.

193
00:12:08,467 --> 00:12:12,533
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

194
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:15,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

195
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:23,300
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

196
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:26,167
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

197
00:12:29,433 --> 00:12:31,200
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

198
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:36,900
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

199
00:12:42,167 --> 00:12:44,700
Ma'am Marj,
what are you doing here?

200
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:46,667
May I come in?

201
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:50,400
Ash.

202
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:55,167
What are you doing here?

203
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:58,033
I told you to stay away
from me for now.

204
00:12:58,167 --> 00:13:00,600
You should know
I wouldn't do that, Ash.

205
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:02,367
What?

206
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,867
You never gave up on me,
remember?

207
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,767
When I was sick,

208
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:09,767
even when I snapped at you,
you never left my side.

209
00:13:11,233 --> 00:13:13,033
I'm just returning the favor.

210
00:13:14,433 --> 00:13:17,033
I won't give up on you, Ash.

211
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:20,100
Che and Weng really needs
some scolding.

212
00:13:20,233 --> 00:13:24,767
I already told them
not to tell anyone where I am.

213
00:13:24,933 --> 00:13:27,400
Ms. Yolly, please don't be angry
at them.

214
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:29,133
I was the one who insisted.

215
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:32,533
I'm here because I want to ask
for your help.

216
00:13:32,667 --> 00:13:34,300
If it's possible for you
to give a statement

217
00:13:34,433 --> 00:13:37,000
for the preliminary
investigation.

218
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:40,267
Edward told me
that you saw him enter the room

219
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,167
before the fire happened.

220
00:13:44,767 --> 00:13:46,700
Is that the only reason
you came here?

221
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:51,400
You're just wasting time
and effort.

222
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:54,800
I don't want to get involved
with the Torrecampos anymore.

223
00:13:54,967 --> 00:13:58,733
If you're truly angry
at the Torrecampos,

224
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:02,967
admit it, Edward treated you
kindly, didn't he?

225
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:06,200
That's no longer my problem.

226
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:09,300
Why are you so persistent?

227
00:14:09,433 --> 00:14:10,967
It's just a favor, cousin.

228
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,900
Don't push me away.

229
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:15,833
My balance is still weak.

230
00:14:19,467 --> 00:14:20,833
And if possible,

231
00:14:20,967 --> 00:14:23,267
stop pushing Xander
to pursue me.

232
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,067
Just because I can walk now
and we're close.

233
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,267
Why not?

234
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:29,900
You liked him first, didn't you?

235
00:14:30,067 --> 00:14:32,133
That was before, Ash.

236
00:14:32,267 --> 00:14:36,100
But I don't like Xander anymore.
You're more important to me.

237
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:39,500
So please, stop driving me away.

238
00:14:39,633 --> 00:14:43,500
Do you want Edward jailed even
though you know he's innocent?

239
00:14:46,067 --> 00:14:50,567
How can you be sure
that he didn't start the fire?

240
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:53,133
Because I know Edward.

241
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:56,600
He would never do that
to his child.

242
00:14:56,733 --> 00:15:01,700
And even if he did, he would
make sure Ashley wasn't there.

243
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:03,433
Ms. Yolly, if you could only see

244
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:05,333
how much Edward is suffering
right now

245
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:07,767
because of what happened
to Ashley,

246
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:12,633
you would believe
he could never burn a house

247
00:15:12,767 --> 00:15:15,967
knowing someone could get hurt.

248
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:19,400
There's the door.

249
00:15:19,533 --> 00:15:20,900
Leave now.

250
00:15:21,033 --> 00:15:24,400
You can leave
and don't come back.

251
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:29,467
What are you doing here?

252
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,133
Stay away from my child.

253
00:15:31,267 --> 00:15:33,700
You might give her some virus.

254
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:36,200
Leave now!

255
00:15:36,367 --> 00:15:38,767
Go on!

256
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:40,633
Leave!

257
00:15:40,767 --> 00:15:43,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

258
00:15:48,467 --> 00:15:52,367
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:55,400
I'm sorry, Auntie. I was just...

260
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:57,733
Don't go near my child again.

261
00:15:57,867 --> 00:16:00,033
Get out!

262
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,033
Ashley?

263
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,767
Don't hurt Jasmine!

264
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:05,833
I don't care!

265
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:07,267
- [GRUNTING]
- Ash!

266
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,500
- Ashley!
- [GRUNTING]

267
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:11,767
[GRUNTING]

268
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,267
Stay away from my child!

269
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,167
Can't you see what you've done?

270
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:17,367
- I'm sorry.
- I'm okay, Mom.

271
00:16:17,500 --> 00:16:20,133
What do you mean okay?
My child, what's wrong with you?

272
00:16:20,267 --> 00:16:23,500
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:16:23,633 --> 00:16:25,800
Nurse! Nurse, we need help.

274
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,233
[GRUNTING]

275
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:32,167
[SOBBING]

276
00:16:35,467 --> 00:16:38,200
Edward, I wanted to beg her.

277
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:42,100
But Ms. Yolly sent me away.
She really refuses to testify.

278
00:16:42,267 --> 00:16:44,167
["KATOTOHANAN"
INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

279
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,567
I don't want to force her.

280
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:50,933
Don't worry, I'll try again.
I'll find a way to convince her.

281
00:16:51,067 --> 00:16:53,233
Your sibling has already spoken
to your lawyer.

282
00:16:53,367 --> 00:16:56,933
There might be a legal way
to force her to testify.

283
00:16:57,067 --> 00:16:59,667
Thank you to you and Paolo.

284
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,467
I don't know
what I'd do without you.

285
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:04,767
Of course we won't abandon you.

286
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:07,000
And I know your sibling
just wants to prove to you

287
00:17:07,133 --> 00:17:09,400
that he's not like your father.

288
00:17:09,533 --> 00:17:12,200
We're doing everything
to win this.

289
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:19,167
I just want this to end
as soon as possible.

290
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:20,867
I want to go back to Ashley.

291
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:24,533
It's been days
since she last saw me,

292
00:17:24,667 --> 00:17:26,767
and my child really needs me.

293
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:32,700
I thought you invited
many prospective clients.

294
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:34,600
There aren't even a dozen people
inside.

295
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:36,667
Do you even have a brain?

296
00:17:39,033 --> 00:17:40,767
How many do you think will buy?

297
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:42,733
There are a lot inside.

298
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:45,500
Albert...

299
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:47,367
leave us for now.

300
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:55,433
You're meddling.

301
00:17:55,567 --> 00:17:57,967
Maybe you forgot
you're no longer the CEO here.

302
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,400
You know,

303
00:18:00,533 --> 00:18:02,433
if you keep acting like that,

304
00:18:02,567 --> 00:18:05,033
even if you were CEO,

305
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:07,400
no one would respect you.

306
00:18:07,533 --> 00:18:10,500
Respect our employees.

307
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:13,767
Don't ruin the Torrecampo name.

308
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:19,933
You're still extremely proud of
being a Torrecampo, aren't you?

309
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:26,100
Where do you think you'll end up

310
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:28,333
once that name is taken away
from you?

311
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,600
What do you mean?

312
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:35,033
What I mean is,

313
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:38,233
don't act arrogant with me.

314
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:41,267
Because the Torrecampos
are no longer respected here.

315
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:45,500
With all the scandals and dirt
surrounding your family,

316
00:18:45,633 --> 00:18:47,300
people are just laughing at you.

317
00:18:48,867 --> 00:18:51,500
People like you...

318
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:53,767
are no longer respected.

319
00:18:56,800 --> 00:19:02,000
The next time
you insult our family again,

320
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:03,867
I will make you regret it.

321
00:19:06,033 --> 00:19:09,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

322
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:19,300
<i> You're wrong, Paolo.</i>

323
00:19:19,433 --> 00:19:22,867
<i>You will be the one to regret
your arrogance.</i>

324
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,500
<i> Once you learn the truth.</i>

325
00:19:24,633 --> 00:19:26,500
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

326
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:19:45,233 --> 00:19:47,667
You don't need to worry
about that anymore.

328
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:50,933
<i>Do you want Edward
to be imprisoned</i>

329
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:53,500
<i>even when you know
he's innocent?</i>

330
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:56,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

331
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,933
Thank you so much, Attorney.

332
00:20:03,100 --> 00:20:05,033
Please keep me updated
on the progress of the case.

333
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:06,533
Of course.

334
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:20,033
Paolo.

335
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:31,367
I just came by to apologize
for earlier.

336
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:34,500
I didn't mean to lash out
at our employee.

337
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:36,333
I take full accountability.

338
00:20:38,233 --> 00:20:39,600
Just don't do it again.

339
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:41,833
Wait, Paolo.

340
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,567
I don't mean to pry,

341
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:47,533
but was it your lawyer
you were talking to earlier?

342
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:49,367
Is this about Edward?

343
00:20:51,733 --> 00:20:52,933
Dad.

344
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:56,300
Ashley?

345
00:20:57,333 --> 00:20:58,767
My child,

346
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,967
I'm glad you're out
of the hospital.

347
00:21:03,267 --> 00:21:04,567
Thank you.

348
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,167
My child,

349
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:11,200
I almost went crazy worrying
about how you were doing.

350
00:21:11,367 --> 00:21:12,567
How are you now?

351
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:15,067
I'm okay, Dad. How about you?

352
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:22,500
I know you could never do
what they accused you of.

353
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:28,000
You wouldn't burn the house
just out of anger.

354
00:21:32,233 --> 00:21:33,500
Don't worry.

355
00:21:34,567 --> 00:21:36,667
The truth will come out.

356
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,467
I'll get out of here too,
my child.

357
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:42,000
Just mind your own business.

358
00:21:42,167 --> 00:21:43,733
Forgive me, Paolo, but...

359
00:21:43,867 --> 00:21:46,467
I think I may have a solution

360
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:49,400
to have his case dismissed.

361
00:21:49,533 --> 00:21:54,767
Sir Greg will surely withdraw
the case and release Edward

362
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:57,333
once he learns the truth.

363
00:21:57,467 --> 00:22:01,100
What if I'm the one who talks
to Grandfather Greg?

364
00:22:01,233 --> 00:22:03,067
Maybe if I'm the one
who asks him,

365
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:07,200
he'll withdraw the arson case.
Maybe he'll listen to me.

366
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:09,233
Stop being naive, Ashley.

367
00:22:09,367 --> 00:22:12,333
He doesn't even see us
as family.

368
00:22:12,467 --> 00:22:15,267
When you needed surgery,
did he help?

369
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:16,533
No, right?

370
00:22:16,667 --> 00:22:20,367
That's why he doesn't care
if your father rots in jail.

371
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:24,600
- Thea, that's enough.
- It's the truth.

372
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:27,033
He has always recognized
only one child and heir

373
00:22:27,167 --> 00:22:30,300
from then until now,
and that's Paolo.

374
00:22:31,567 --> 00:22:34,100
But Paolo...

375
00:22:34,233 --> 00:22:35,800
treated me as family.

376
00:22:35,933 --> 00:22:37,567
He and Marj.

377
00:22:37,700 --> 00:22:39,733
They are the ones
supporting me now.

378
00:22:39,867 --> 00:22:43,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

379
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:49,800
What do you mean?

380
00:22:53,267 --> 00:22:54,467
In fact,

381
00:22:55,733 --> 00:22:57,567
I may be doing you a favor.

382
00:22:58,533 --> 00:23:02,533
Actually, what I'm about to tell
you is also for your own good.

383
00:23:02,667 --> 00:23:06,733
So you won't remain clueless
about your true identity.

384
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:10,100
Can you just be direct with me?

385
00:23:10,233 --> 00:23:11,600
Well, what about their promise

386
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:14,967
that they would handle
Ms. Yolly's cooperation?

387
00:23:15,100 --> 00:23:16,533
You'll just rot in jail,

388
00:23:16,667 --> 00:23:18,133
and they still
can't be relied on.

389
00:23:18,267 --> 00:23:20,600
Thea, they're doing everything
they can.

390
00:23:20,733 --> 00:23:23,100
If I were you,
go talk to Paolo and Marj.

391
00:23:23,267 --> 00:23:24,800
- What?
- Follow up with them.

392
00:23:25,933 --> 00:23:30,100
Only Paolo and Marj have a way
to help me get out of here.

393
00:23:30,233 --> 00:23:33,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

394
00:23:41,367 --> 00:23:43,700
Edward is not
an illegitimate child.

395
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:47,800
He was not the result
of your mother's affair.

396
00:23:49,633 --> 00:23:51,367
It's you, Paolo.

397
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:54,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

398
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:59,400
You are the real illegitimate
child of your mother.

399
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:02,800
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

400
00:24:04,033 --> 00:24:06,567
Ms. Yolly,
what are you doing here?

401
00:24:06,700 --> 00:24:09,333
Miss Yolly Natividad is here
to give a statement.

402
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:11,467
She claims she knows
something about your case.

403
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:15,400
How can you be sure that she had
nothing to do with the fire?

404
00:24:15,533 --> 00:24:18,000
I know who really did it.

405
00:24:18,133 --> 00:24:19,833
Who, Ms. Yolly?

406
00:24:19,967 --> 00:24:22,500
Did someone else enter the house
that night?

407
00:24:22,633 --> 00:24:24,633
Was Aldrin responsible for this?

408
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:26,333
Mom, don't worry.

409
00:24:26,467 --> 00:24:28,433
I already filed a complaint
against him.

410
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:30,800
I'll teach him a lesson
so he'll stop.

411
00:24:30,933 --> 00:24:33,233
Don't go through with it.

412
00:24:33,367 --> 00:24:35,033
Mom, why?

413
00:24:35,167 --> 00:24:37,900
Do you know what he's been
saying about you?

414
00:24:38,033 --> 00:24:41,233
Paolo has no right to act
like a golden boy,

415
00:24:41,367 --> 00:24:44,067
because he's not
a real Torrecampo.

416
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:46,567
He's just an illegitimate child
of his mother.

417
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:49,667
I'm sorry, Edward,
that I couldn't help you before.

418
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:52,033
That's why I'm here now
to make up for it.

419
00:24:52,167 --> 00:24:53,067
Leave now.

420
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,967
Listen first
to what she has to say.

421
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:56,367
What is she talking about?

422
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:57,767
Well, lucky for you...

423
00:24:57,900 --> 00:25:00,233
I know exactly
where he'll be tonight.

424
00:25:00,367 --> 00:25:02,367
He's attending
an awarding event.

425
00:25:02,533 --> 00:25:05,233
I'm sure he won't be able
to avoid you

426
00:25:05,367 --> 00:25:07,500
in front of many people.

427
00:25:07,633 --> 00:25:09,000
This is for you, my child.

428
00:25:09,133 --> 00:25:13,033
Is this it?
Is this what you're so proud of

429
00:25:13,167 --> 00:25:16,100
to continue
the Torrecampo legacy?

430
00:25:16,233 --> 00:25:18,733
No. He doesn't deserve it, Dad.

431
00:25:18,867 --> 00:25:23,733
In fact, he shouldn't even
be using the Torrecampo surname.

432
00:25:23,867 --> 00:25:27,667
Dad and the whole world
deserve to know the truth.

433
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:32,200
That this man is the product
of infidelity

434
00:25:32,333 --> 00:25:35,133
by his mother with another man.

435
00:25:36,967 --> 00:25:40,767
He's not your blood, Dad.
He's not your real child.

436
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:45,200
Did you hear that, Dad?

437
00:25:45,333 --> 00:25:49,033
The Torrecampos
are slowly self-destructing.

438
00:25:49,167 --> 00:25:51,933
I can already imagine
your mistress Regina

439
00:25:52,067 --> 00:25:57,333
feeling helpless and powerless
even as everything falls apart.

440
00:25:57,467 --> 00:25:59,700
But I'm not done yet.

441
00:25:59,833 --> 00:26:02,033
I still have many things planned
for her.

442
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:08,333
I was cruel to my real child
because of your lies.

443
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:12,333
I destroyed Edward because
I believed he wasn't my blood.

444
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:15,800
All of that because
of your infidelity!

445
00:26:15,933 --> 00:26:19,767
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
